OL,6,FThe killer later changed his story
OL,7,Fclaiming he was upstairs in the house,
OL,8,Fasleep after taking heroin and crack,
OL,9,Fwhile someone else strangled Mr
OL,10,FPatience downstairs.
OL,12,FMichael Hayton KC, prosecuting, said
OL,13,FConnell preyed upon the good nature of
OL,14,FMr Patience, who had access to cash
OL,15,Ffrom family property.
OL,17,FHe said the defendant used Mr Patience
OL,18,Fas an "open wallet" in receiving
OL,19,Fthousands of pounds since they first
OL,20,Fmet.
